    {
      "id": "f10d76fc18c14e108137633d4d8642f648edbae1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-28 06:59:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nwhile I find this cleanup great, I'd like to clarify a bit. \n\nas precreated objects are not subject to reuse and currently every reconnect to OST is considered as a remount (sort of no state is preserved over reconnection), I'd say that:\n1) opd_pre_last_created  should not matter until the first precreate after reconnection.\n2) no objects should be available till first completed precreation after reconnection.\n\nthis probably means http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,4590 should be reworked as well. need to think more ..",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "0c9f9e1242ac95d110050f131e6c4d013b916ae8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
